functions.label: Navigation
signature: ({ children, homeRef, unstyled = false, dataTestSubj }: Props) => JSX.Element

functions.label: NavigationKibanaProvider
description: Kibana-specific Provider that maps dependencies to services.

functions.label: NavigationProvider
description: A Context Provider that provides services to the component and its dependencies.

interfaces.label: ChromeNavigation
description: External definition of the side navigation.

children.label: homeLink
description: Target for the logo icon. Must be an app id or a deeplink id.

children.label: linkToCloud
description: Control of the link that takes the user to their projects or deployments

children.label: navigationTree
description:
The navigation tree definition.

NOTE: For now this tree will _only_ contain the solution tree and we will concatenate
the different platform trees inside the <Navigation /> component.
In a following work we will build the full navigation tree inside a "buildNavigationTree()"
helper exposed from this package. This helper will allow an array of PlatformId to be disabled

e.g. buildNavigationTree({ solutionTree: [...], disable: ['devTools'] })

children.label: platformConfig
description:
Controls over which Platform nav sections is enabled or disabled.
NOTE: this is a temporary solution until we have the buildNavigationTree() helper mentioned
above.

children.label: recentlyAccessedFilter
description: Filter function to allow consumer to remove items from the recently accessed section

interfaces.label: ChromeNavigationNode
description: Chrome navigatioin node definition.

children.label: id
description: An optional id. If not provided a link must be passed

children.label: title
description: An optional title for the node
signature: boolean | React.ReactChild | React.ReactFragment | React.ReactPortal | null | undefined

children.label: icon
description: An optional eui icon

children.label: link
description: An app id or a deeplink id

children.label: items
description: Sub navigation item for this node

interfaces.label: ChromeNavigationNodeViewModel
description:
Chrome navigation definition used internally in the components.
Each "link" (if present) has been converted to a propert href. Additional metadata has been added
like the "isActive" flag or the "path" (indicating the full path of the node in the nav tree).

children.label: path
description:
Full path that points to this node (includes all parent ids). If not set
the path is the id

children.label: defaultIsCollapsed
description: Flag to indicate if the group is initially collapsed or not.

interfaces.label: NavigationServices
description: A list of services that are consumed by this component.

children.label: body
description:
Main content of the navigation. Can contain any number of "cloudLink", "recentlyAccessed"
or "group" items. Be mindeful though, with great power comes great responsibility.

children.label: footer
description:
Footer content of the navigation. Can contain any number of "cloudLink", "recentlyAccessed"
or "group" items. Be mindeful though, with great power comes great responsibility.

children.label: id
description: Optional id, if not passed a "link" must be provided.

children.label: title
description: Optional title. If not provided and a "link" is provided the title will be the Deep link title

children.label: link
description: App id or deeplink id

children.label: icon
description: Optional icon for the navigation node. Note: not all navigation depth will render the icon

children.label: children
description: Optional children of the navigation node

children.label: href
description:
Temporarilly we allow href to be passed.
Once all the deeplinks will be exposed in packages we will not allow href anymore
and force deeplink id to be passed

children.label: homeRef
description: The URL href for the home link

children.label: projectNavigationTree
description:
A navigation tree structure with object items containing labels, links, and sub-items
for a project. Use it if you only need to configure your project navigation and leave
all the other navigation items to the default (Recently viewed items, Management, etc.)

children.label: navigationTree
description:
A navigation tree structure with object items containing labels, links, and sub-items
that defines a complete side navigation. This configuration overrides `projectNavigationTree`
if both are provided.

misc.label: NavigationGroupPreset
description: The preset that can be pass to the NavigationBucket component
